verbose_text: Although TIFAB increased the reaction rate of USP15 cleavage of its preferred ubiquitin linked chains, incubation of TIFAB did not result in USP15 mediated cleavage of K27, K29, and linear ubiquitins (XREF_FIG), indicating that TIFAB does not change the linkage preferences of USP15.
evidence: TIFAB increased the reaction rate of USP15
